<p>Addressing an <a href="https://old.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/w761d3/how_to_automatically_collapse_attachments_in/">innocuous question</a> about the Notmuch email client’s default behavior took me surprisingly deep into the bowels of the package code.  When the normal customization methods didn’t help, I realized it might be a good opportunity to live-code a solution.</p>
<p>The hope was that it might outline a recipe for reaching into the elisp guts of any library and getting Emacs to do what you want –  with no specific prior knowledge.  The reality is thirty minutes of fairly myopic yakshaving:</p>
<a href="https://www.youtube.com/embed/UP2dFk5_ytY">[Video]</a>